        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 6:19AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 618 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of Marshall, or near Hot Springs, moving east at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Faust, Allenstand, Walnut, Wolf Ridge, Marshall, Mars Hill, Hot
Springs, and Spring Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
